<paragraph id="8BDC369AFFFEFF91FF5DF882FBFA2027" blockId="75.[163,779,1845,1898]" lastBlockId="75.[827,1442,197,342]" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFEFF91FF5DF882FE93263B" box="[163,308,1845,1866]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">Distribution:</emphasis>
Only known from 
<typeStatus id="54D88838FFFEFF91FDE9F881FDEF263A" box="[535,584,1846,1867]" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">type</typeStatus>
locality reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B6BFFFEFF91FF3DF8E3FEC3261B" author="Roewer CF" box="[195,356,1876,1898]" pageId="75" pageNumber="660" pagination="106 - 132" refId="ref54383" refString="Roewer CF. 1915 [' 1914 ']. Funfzehn neue Opilioniden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, Abt. A, Original-Arbeiten 80: 106 - 132." type="journal article" year="1915">Roewer (1915)</bibRefCitation>
, which is in Humid Pampas ecoregion in Bahia Blanca, 
<collectingCountry id="F374760AFFFEFF91FBEFFF72FB2C21AA" box="[1041,1163,197,219]" name="Argentina" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFFFEFF91FB60FF72FB5621AB" box="[1182,1265,197,219]" captionStart="Figure 48" captionStartId="64.[145,226,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[147,1428,447,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-112@64.[145,1428,445,1719]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="Figure 48. Map of known distribution of Gryne. Numbers correspond to the following WWF ecoregions: 1 = Uatumã- Trombetas moist forest, 2 = Madeira-Tapajós moist forest, 3 = Xingú-Tocantins-Araguaia moist forest, 4 = Marajó várzea, 5 = Tocantins/Pindaré moist forest, 6 = Mato grosso seasonal forest, 7 = Caatinga, 8 = Pernambuco Coastal forest, 9 = Cerrado, 10 = Bahia interior forest, 11 = Bahia coastal forest, 12 = Alto Paraná Atlantic forest, 13 = Pantanal, 14 = Dry Chaco, 15 = Humid chaco, 16 = Parana flooded savanna, 17 = Humid pampas." pageId="75" pageNumber="660">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
). This locality is probably incorrect and maybe the material used by Roewer was sent from the ancient port of Bahia Blanca and that is why it is on the label (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFFFEFF91FAF4FE96FACF2046" box="[1290,1384,289,311]" captionStart="Figure 56" captionStartId="76.[145,223,779,801]" captionTargetBox="[337,1233,195,739]" captionTargetId="figure-23@76.[337,1233,195,739]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="Figure 56. Gryne marmorata, female syntype (SMF RI 1076). A, dorsal view. B, latero dorsal view. C, original label. Photos courtesy Ricardo Pinto-da-Rocha." pageId="75" pageNumber="660">Fig. 56C</figureCitation>
), but collected somewhere else.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFFFEFF91FCC5FEC9FA312275" blockId="75.[827,1443,382,772]" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFEFF91FCC5FEC9FC0820E2" box="[827,943,382,403]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">Remarks:</emphasis>
Although this species was not used as a terminal in the present analysis, examination of photographs of 
<typeStatus id="54D88838FFFEFF91FC0CFE0BFB8320A0" box="[1010,1060,444,465]" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">type</typeStatus>
of this species – in an advanced stage of this project – allows us to recognize it as a member of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFEFF91FC41FE4EFBA2237F" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1879" box="[959,1029,505,526]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Gryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="75" pageNumber="660" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFEFF91FC41FE4EFBA2237F" box="[959,1029,505,526]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">Gryne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[and not 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFEFF91FB87FE4EFB5A237F" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1839" box="[1145,1277,505,526]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Paecilaema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="75" pageNumber="660" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFEFF91FB87FE4EFB5A237F" box="[1145,1277,505,526]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">Paecilaema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as diagnosed in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B6BFFFEFF91FCA6FDAFFBC0235F" author="Medrano M &amp; Kury AB" box="[856,1127,536,558]" pageId="75" pageNumber="660" pagination="1206 - 1233" refId="ref53005" refString="Medrano M, Kury AB. 2018. Relationships and cladistic analysis of Roquettea with description of two new species and notes about evolution of stylus in Cosmetidae (Opiliones, Grassatores). Invertebrate Systematics 32: 1206 - 1233." type="journal article" year="2018">Kury &amp; Medrano (2018)</bibRefCitation>
]. However, the photographs (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFFFEFF91FCBDFD81FC28233D" box="[835,911,566,588]" captionStart="Figure 56" captionStartId="76.[145,223,779,801]" captionTargetBox="[337,1233,195,739]" captionTargetId="figure-23@76.[337,1233,195,739]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="Figure 56. Gryne marmorata, female syntype (SMF RI 1076). A, dorsal view. B, latero dorsal view. C, original label. Photos courtesy Ricardo Pinto-da-Rocha." pageId="75" pageNumber="660">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
) do not allow us to detect a possible synonymy with any member of 
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFEFF91FBD4FDE2FBD1231B" box="[1066,1142,597,618]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFEFF91FBD4FDE2FBD5231B" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1879" box="[1066,1138,597,618]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Gryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="75" pageNumber="660" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Gryne</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The only species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFEFF91FAA0FDE2FA04231B" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1879" box="[1374,1443,597,618]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Gryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="75" pageNumber="660" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFEFF91FAA0FDE2FA04231B" box="[1374,1443,597,618]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">Gryne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurring in 
<collectingCountry id="F374760AFFFEFF91FC33FDC3FBE523FB" box="[973,1090,628,650]" name="Argentina" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">Argentina</collectingCountry>
is 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFEFF91FB9BFDC3FB7223F8" baseAuthorityName="Sorensen" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[1125,1237,628,649]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Gryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="75" pageNumber="660" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orensis">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFEFF91FB9BFDC3FB7223F8" box="[1125,1237,628,649]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">G. orensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF24B6BFFFEFF91FB1CFDC3FA0423FB" author="Ringuelet RA" box="[1250,1443,628,650]" pageId="75" pageNumber="660" pagination="127 - 439" refId="ref54272" refString="Ringuelet RA. 1959. Los aracnidos Argentinos del orden Opiliones. Revista del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales ' Bernardino Rivadavia' 5: 127 - 439, figs 1 - 62, plates 1 - 20." type="journal article" year="1959">Ringuelet (1959)</bibRefCitation>
examined 
<typeStatus id="54D88838FFFEFF91FC4DFD24FC4223D9" box="[947,997,659,680]" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">type</typeStatus>
material of both 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFEFF91FB4CFD24FA8323D9" baseAuthorityName="Sorensen" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[1202,1316,659,680]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Gryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="75" pageNumber="660" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orensis">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFEFF91FB4CFD24FA8323D9" box="[1202,1316,659,680]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">G. orensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(described by him as 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFEFF91FC48FD05FBEF23B7" authorityName="Ringuelet" authorityYear="1957" box="[950,1096,689,711]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Paecilaema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="75" pageNumber="660" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neglectum">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFEFF91FC48FD05FBEF23B7" box="[950,1096,689,711]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">P. neglectum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and here considered a junior synonym) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FFFEFF91FC10FD67FB342394" authorityName="Medrano &amp; Kury &amp; Mendes" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Roewer" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[1006,1171,720,741]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Gryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="75" pageNumber="660" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FFFEFF91FC10FD67FB342394" box="[1006,1171,720,741]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="660">P. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and did not recognize such similarity as to consider them the same species.
</paragraph>
